🔹 Router (Internetwork Operating System – IOS)
1. What is a Router?

        English: A router is a network device that connects different networks together and decides the best path for data to travel.
        
        Hindi: Router ek aisa device hai jo alag-alag networks ko jodta hai aur data packet ko bhejne ke liye best rasta choose karta hai.

👉 Switch = ek hi network ke andar devices connect karta hai.
👉 Router = alag networks ko connect karta hai.

2. Why Router is Important?

        Without routers, your LAN (ghar/office network) can’t talk to another LAN (like your friend’s home or Google’s servers).
        
        Jaise tumhare ghar ka WiFi Router tumhara local network (phone/laptop) ko Internet (world network) se jodta hai.

3. What is Router IOS?

        IOS = Internetwork Operating System
        
        Ye ek software hai jo router ke andar chalta hai.
        
        Isi ke through hum configure karte hain router ko (via CLI commands).
        
        Example: ip route, show running-config etc.

👉 Hindi: Router ek box hai, aur IOS uska dimaag (brain) hai.
Without IOS, router ek khaali dabba hai.

4. Functions of a Router

        Packet Forwarding → data ko best path se bhejna.
        
        Path Selection → routing protocols use karke best route decide karna.
        
        Internetworking → alag networks (LAN–WAN–Internet) ko connect karna.
        
        Security → ACLs, firewall rules apply karna.
        
        Addressing → IP addresses ko samajhna aur unke basis pe decision lena.

5. Router Interfaces

        LAN Interface (Ethernet/FastEthernet/Gigabit) → local network connect karne ke liye.
        
        WAN Interface (Serial, Fiber, DSL) → Internet ya dusre remote network ke liye.

6. Example (Relatable)

        📩 Tum ek WhatsApp message bhejte ho →
        
        Mobile → WiFi Router (LAN)
        
        WiFi Router → ISP Router (WAN)
        
        ISP Router → Internet Backbone → Destination ISP Router
        
        Destination Router → Friend’s WiFi Router → Friend’s mobile

👉 Har router apna routing table check karta hai aur packet ko aage bhejta hai.

7. How Router Decides the Path?

        Routers use Routing Tables.
        
        Static Routing → manually set path.
        
        Dynamic Routing → automatic via protocols (RIP, OSPF, EIGRP, BGP).

8. One-Line Summary

        Router = Network ka Traffic Police 🚦
        
        Har packet ko check karta hai → “Kaha jaana hai?” aur phir best road choose karke bhej deta hai.
        
        IOS = Router ka Operating System (uska dimaag 🧠) jisse hum usko configure karte hain.
